## New Findings This Run

### OXPHOS Drug Validation (journal #14) — Negative/Weak Result
- IACS-10759 (CI inhibitor) and tigecycline (mitoribo inhibitor) tested in PRISM
- Metformin and venetoclax NOT in PRISM — cannot test clinically relevant agents
- Pan-cancer: d≈-0.2 for both drugs (trend but NOT significant, FDR>0.36)
- Uterus/IACS-10759: d=-0.764 but underpowered (n=9 MSI-H)
- Within-MSI-H concordance: tigecycline sens correlates with COX5A CRISPR dep (r=-0.353, p=0.038) and TFAM (r=-0.341, p=0.045)
- CRISPR genetic evidence (Fisher p=3.32e-08) remains stronger than pharmacological

### DHX9 as Novel MSI-H Target (journal #15) — NOVEL FINDING
- Pan-cancer d=-0.933, p=7.19e-06; Bowel d=-1.682, p=1.07e-05
- ONLY RNA helicase with MSI-H selectivity (8 tested)
- Independent of WRN (r=0.047 all lines) — orthogonal R-loop mechanism
- 100% MSI-H lines dependent (vs 95.1% MSS)
- No RNA helicase inhibitors exist yet — pre-clinical opportunity
- Created research_director task #49

